ADDRESS INFO for George Isiah Washington
Current: 10946 W. FLORIST AVE, Milwaukee, WI 53225-2406 United States  (Effective: 03-16-2016)
Prior: 7800 West Fond Du Lac Avenue # 104, Milwaukee, WI 53218

Defendant George Isiah Washington in court with attorney Derek H. Goodman.  Christopher Allen Liegel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
To the charged offense:    Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms/body armor.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.   
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the state, defense and defendant.
The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 3 days in the House of Correction, with credit for 3 days time served.  
Court ordered defendant to pay a fine of $100.00 PLUS all applicable court costs, fees and assessments, DNA surcharge by 11-12-2015, or a civil judgment shall be entered.
Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample, if not already provided, and pay the DNA fees and surcharges, if not already paid,  by 11-12-2015, or to be docketed as a civil judgment.
